# Cards.elm — agent-side card predicates

Thin module of pure predicates the BFS planner needs that
don't already exist in `Game.Rules.Card` / `Game.Rules.StackType`. Lives
inside the Agent namespace so it doesn't disturb the
INTRICATE existing modules.

## Status

- **Label:** WORKHORSE.
- **Mirrors:** `python/cards.py` § `partial_ok`,
  `neighbors`, plus a thin alias for `classify` →
  `isLegalStack`.

## Key exports

- `isLegalStack : List Card -> Bool` — wraps
  `Game.Rules.StackType.getStackType`. True iff the result is
  `Set | PureRun | RedBlackRun`.
- `isPartialOk : List Card -> Bool` — the
  "could-this-extend?" predicate. Empty + singleton are
  trivially OK; length-2 pairs are OK if they pair up as a
  valid run-partial or set-partial; length-3+ delegates to
  `isLegalStack`.
- `neighbors : Card -> List ( CardValue, Suit )` — every
  (value, suit) shape that could legally sit adjacent to
  `c` in some valid group (pure run, rb run, or set).
  Deck-agnostic.

## Pointers

- Python source: `python/cards.py`.
- Tests: `tests/Game/Agent/CardsTest.elm`.
